# Topology Creator - Cursor Rules
# ================================
# These rules must be followed for ALL development in the Topology Creator project.

## 🚫 NO EMOJIS RULE (CRITICAL)

**NEVER use emojis anywhere in this codebase.**

### Why:
- Emojis render inconsistently across platforms and browsers
- They add unnecessary bytes and complexity
- SVG icons are more professional and customizable
- Emojis can break in certain terminal/console environments

### Instead of emojis:
1. **For UI elements**: Use SVG icons from the icon library in index.html
   - All icons are defined in `<svg style="display:none">` at the top of index.html
   - Reference them with: `<svg><use href="#ico-iconname"/></svg>`
   - Available icons: ico-alert, ico-bug, ico-warning, ico-error, ico-success, ico-info, 
     ico-network, ico-link, ico-router, ico-discover, ico-copy, ico-edit, ico-delete, 
     ico-save, ico-refresh, ico-close, ico-check, ico-palette, ico-label, ico-lock, 
     ico-unlock, ico-pin, ico-target, ico-chart, ico-layers, ico-curve, ico-brush, 
     ico-sparkle, ico-text, ico-search, ico-list, ico-import, ico-ruler, ico-up, 
     ico-down, ico-left, ico-right, ico-menu, ico-play, ico-magnet, ico-hand, 
     ico-rocket, ico-spectrum, ico-image, ico-minus, ico-gear

2. **For debug/log messages**: Use text prefixes like:
   - `[OK]` instead of ✅
   - `[WARN]` instead of ⚠️
   - `[ERROR]` instead of ❌
   - `[INFO]` instead of ℹ️
   - Descriptive text like `"Drag Started"` instead of `"🎯 Drag Started"`

3. **For status indicators**: Use CSS-styled elements or text
   - Colors work better than emojis for status
   - Use CSS classes for visual states

### Adding new icons:
If you need an icon that doesn't exist:
1. Add a new `<symbol>` in the SVG defs section of index.html
2. Use consistent viewBox (24x24 is standard)
3. Use currentColor for fills to inherit text color
4. Follow the duotone pattern with opacity layers for depth

---

## File Structure

- `index.html` - Main HTML with SVG icon library
- `topology.js` - Core topology canvas logic
- `styles.css` - All CSS styling with CSS variables for theming
- `server.py` - FastAPI backend server

## CSS Theming

Use CSS variables for all colors:
- `--dn-navy-deep` - Primary dark background
- `--dn-cyan` - Primary accent color
- `--dn-orange` - Secondary accent/action color  
- `--dn-cloud` - Light text/background
- Reference styles.css for full color palette

## Canvas Drawing

When drawing on canvas:
- Use the existing drawing methods in TopologyCanvas class
- Maintain consistent styling with theme colors
- Use professional fonts (DM Sans, Space Grotesk, etc.)
- Avoid hardcoded colors - use this.* properties

## Code Style

- Use ES6+ JavaScript features
- Maintain 4-space indentation in JS
- Use descriptive variable names
- Comment complex logic
- Keep functions focused and small






